5:
You said there'd be nice sake at the
end of this...
8:
But the sun's about to go down, and
you're still not finished.
12:
If you're gonna complain, then at
least lend us a hand!
17:
The faster we finish, the faster you'll
get your alcohol!
21: Must be rough to be so weak, eh?
24: Guess I don't have a choice.
35: We'll have to spend the night here.
39:
Yeah, no way we're getting past that
sandstorm out there.
44:
If only we had a master of the winds
with us who could blow it away. Now
that sake'll have to wait until
tomorrow.
49:
You really expect me to work my
magic on your behalf?
52:
It's just a day or two. You want me to
fight nature over that?
56:
Says the guy who was telling us to
hurry so he could drink.
60:
This and that are two different
things.
63:
We can't fight back, or they'll kill us...
What do we do?
66: Excuse me. Is something the matter?
73:
...So either the villagers hand over
their food stores willingly, or the
bandits take it by force.
77:
These bandits are small-time if all
they're asking for is food.
81:
This is no laughing matter. I can't
imagine this village has any stores
to spare...
84:
They are stuck between starvation
and bloodshed. We need to help
them.
88:
Gouran, what are you planning to
do?
92: Nothing, of course. I'm no fool.
103:
Because I want to. Isn't it normal to
help out people in trouble?
110:
You'll end up being no different from
those bandits.
119:
You're getting your point across by
force. So are they.
122:
If they lose, they're the weak ones.
They'll starve and die. If they win, the
villagers die instead. Someone dies
either way, so why bother?
127:
...You frame it as a struggle for
survival, which it is.
130:
But someone must step in if they are
to have any hope of stopping the
cycle of violence.
134:
What can you possibly hope to do
as weaklings yourselves?
138:
Whatever we can, because that's
what weaklings like us dostruggle
no matter the odds.
147: See? I'll protect you no matter what
152:
Fine. Do what you will. This has
nothing to do with me.
156:
Yeah, that's about the response 
I expected.
165:
Sure am. Let's get this over with 
so I can hit the hay early.
170:
Hmph... This poor village only sells
the cheap stuff.
176:
There's no point dredging up old
memories like that.
183: Come on, is this really all you got?
186:
There's only two of them, and a lot of
us! Get 'em!
190:
Back off, or else this kid gets a knife
in the ribs!
201: Gouran? What are you doing here?
205:
Don't mind me. I'm just having an
evening walk to sober up.
208:
Y-you'll pay for what you did to the
boss!
211:
What's this? A bunch of pesky flies
buzzing around?
220:
He wrapped everything up in one
attack... Sheesh...
227:
...Thank you for rescuing those
children, Gouran.
231: All I did was swat a few pests away.
234: On a whim, even. So don't thank me.
239: ...You really expect us to believe that?
243:
Course I do. I'm a tengu, through
and through, or did you forget that?
